[DOCUMENT]
TITLE: Software component implementation and testing
OPTIONS:
  MARKUP: Text

[GRAMMAR]
IMPORT_FROM_FILE: en_50716_grammar.sgra

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This document covers the Component Implementation and Testing phase for
the software element of the railway control and protection system identified
below. It is prepared in accordance with EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.5
(Component implementation and testing), and collects three output deliverables
from Table A.1:

  18. Software Source Code and supporting documentation
  19. Software Component Test Report
  20. Software Source Code Verification Report

BASIC and SIL_1 through SIL_4 fields are taken from EN 50716:2023:
- Table A.1 (doc 18, source code): BASIC=HR, SIL_1–4=HR.
- Table A.1 (docs 19, 20, test report and verification report): BASIC=--, SIL_1–4=HR.
- Table A.4 (implementation techniques): values vary per technique.
- Table A.5 (analysis and test results): values vary per technique.

Instructions for use:
- UIDs follow convention: CI-xxx (requirements) and CTR-xxx (test cases).
- CTR-xxx test cases are executed records: VERDICT and ACTUAL_RESULT shall
  be populated upon test execution. The sample entries below show the expected
  format for a completed test report.
- Duplicate CTR entries for each test case executed against the component
  test specification (04_component_design.sdoc, CT-xxx series).
- Delete this instruction block before formal release.
<<<

