[TEST_CASE]
UID: CTR-001
STATUS: Active
TITLE: <COMP-ID> – nominal operation – <brief description>
TEST_TYPE: Unit
PRECONDITIONS: >>>
- <COMP-ID> initialised (state = STATE_IDLE).
- <param_1> set to nominal value <nominal_value> (within [<min>..<max>]).
- <param_2> set to VAL_A.
- No fault flags active.
<<<
STEPS: >>>
1. Set <param_1> = <nominal_value>.
2. Set <param_2> = VAL_A.
3. Call <function_name>(<param_1>, <param_2>, &<param_3>).
4. Record return code and <param_3>.
5. Record component state and fault log.
<<<
EXPECTED_RESULT: >>>
- Return code: OK.
- <param_3> = <expected_value> ± <tolerance>.
- Component state: STATE_RUN.
- No fault log entries.
- Execution time: < <n> µs.
<<<
ACTUAL_RESULT: >>>
- Return code: OK. PASS.
- <param_3> = <measured_value> (<expected_value> ± <tolerance>). WITHIN LIMIT.
- Component state: STATE_RUN. PASS.
- Fault log entries: 0. PASS.
- Execution time: <measured_time> µs (budget: <n> µs). WITHIN LIMIT.
<<<
VERDICT: PASS
DATE_EXECUTED: <YYYY-MM-DD>
TESTER: <Name>
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SRS-020
  ROLE: Verifies

[TEST_CASE]
UID: CTR-002
STATUS: Active
TITLE: <COMP-ID> – boundary values – <brief description>
TEST_TYPE: Unit
PRECONDITIONS: >>>
- <COMP-ID> initialised (state = STATE_IDLE).
- No fault flags active.
<<<
STEPS: >>>
a) <param_1> = <min>: call and record.
b) <param_1> = <max>: call and record.
c) <param_1> = <min - 1>: call and record.
d) <param_1> = <max + 1>: call and record.
<<<
EXPECTED_RESULT: >>>
a) OK; <param_3> = <min_output>.
b) OK; <param_3> = <max_output>.
c) ERR_RANGE; <param_3> unchanged; fault logged.
d) ERR_RANGE; <param_3> unchanged; fault logged.
<<<
ACTUAL_RESULT: >>>
a) <param_1> = <min>: return OK; <param_3> = <measured_min_output>. PASS.
b) <param_1> = <max>: return OK; <param_3> = <measured_max_output>. PASS.
c) <param_1> = <min - 1>: return ERR_RANGE; <param_3> = <unchanged>; fault logged (code <FC-xx>). PASS.
d) <param_1> = <max + 1>: return ERR_RANGE; <param_3> = <unchanged>; fault logged (code <FC-xx>). PASS.
No exception or memory corruption in any case. PASS.
<<<
VERDICT: PASS
DATE_EXECUTED: <YYYY-MM-DD>
