[TEST_CASE]
UID: CTR-003
STATUS: Active
TITLE: <COMP-ID> – fault injection – safe state on hardware error
TEST_TYPE: Unit
PRECONDITIONS: >>>
- <COMP-ID> in STATE_RUN.
- Fault injection available to make <hw_read_function> return ERR_HW.
<<<
STEPS: >>>
1. Inject fault: <hw_read_function> returns ERR_HW.
2. Call <function_name> with valid inputs.
3. Record return code, <param_3>, state, fault log.
4. Remove injection; call again with valid inputs.
5. Record return code and state.
<<<
EXPECTED_RESULT: >>>
Step 3: ERR_HW; safe default on <param_3>; STATE_FAIL; fault log entry.
Step 5: Component in STATE_FAIL; fault must be cleared via reset.
<<<
ACTUAL_RESULT: >>>
Step 3: Return ERR_HW. PASS. <param_3> = <safe_default>. PASS.
        State = STATE_FAIL. PASS.
        Fault log entry: code <FC-xx>, timestamp <HH:MM:SS.mmm>. PASS.
Step 5: Return ERR_HW (fault active). PASS. State = STATE_FAIL. PASS.
        No further output computed. PASS.
No watchdog timeout or memory corruption. PASS.
<<<
VERDICT: PASS
DATE_EXECUTED: <YYYY-MM-DD>
TESTER: <Name>
RELATIONS:
- TYPE: Parent
  VALUE: SRS-020
  ROLE: Verifies

[TEST_CASE]
UID: CTR-004
STATUS: Active
TITLE: <COMP-ID> – interface test – precondition violation detection
TEST_TYPE: Unit
PRECONDITIONS: >>>
- <COMP-ID> initialised.
- Fault corrected per PR-001; source revision <hash> in use.
<<<
STEPS: >>>
1. Call with <param_3> = NULL.
2. Call with <param_2> = invalid enum value (outside {VAL_A, VAL_B, VAL_C}).
3. Call with all parameters valid.
<<<
EXPECTED_RESULT: >>>
Step 1: ERR_RANGE; no NULL dereference; fault logged.
Step 2: ERR_RANGE; <param_3> not written; fault logged.
Step 3: OK; <param_3> = <expected_value>.
<<<
ACTUAL_RESULT: >>>
Step 1: Return ERR_RANGE. PASS. No NULL write; memory check clean. PASS.
        Fault log entry code <FC-xx>. PASS.
Step 2: Return ERR_RANGE. PASS. <param_3> = <unchanged>. PASS.
        Fault log entry code <FC-xx>. PASS.
Step 3: Return OK. PASS. <param_3> = <measured_value>
        (<expected_value> ± <tolerance>). WITHIN LIMIT.
PR-001 fix confirmed effective. PASS.
<<<
VERDICT: PASS
