[[SECTION]]
TITLE: Software Source Code Verification Report

[TEXT]
STATEMENT: >>>
This section constitutes the Software Source Code Verification Report as
required by EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.5 and Table A.1 (document 20). It
records the outcome of independent verification of the source code baseline
(section 2) and the Component Test Report (section 3) before both documents
are formally released.
<<<

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: CI-090
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Verification scope and method
STATEMENT: >>>
The source code verification shall cover all deliverables in this document:

  a) Source Code and supporting documentation (section 2):
       - Baseline integrity: all files listed in CI-010 are present and
         match their registered revisions in the CM system (SP-060).
       - Annotation completeness: all source files carry the mandatory file
         and function header annotations (CI-011).
       - Coding standard compliance: compliance summary (CI-020) is complete
         and all deviations are justified and approved.
       - Modular and structured programming metrics: all within limits (CI-021);
         exceptions documented and approved.
       - Analysable programs: loop bounds annotated, pointer arithmetic
         restricted, language compliance confirmed (CI-022).
       - Static analysis: all safety-relevant warnings resolved (CI-030).
       - Build reproducibility: confirmed (CI-041).

  b) Component Test Report (section 3):
       - All test cases (CTR-xxx) executed with PASS verdict.
       - Coverage objectives (CI-060) met for all components.
       - Dynamic analysis techniques (CI-061) applied correctly.
       - Performance budgets (CI-070) not exceeded.
       - All interface tests (CI-071) PASS.
       - All PRs closed or safety-assessed (CI-080).

Verification method: structured inspection by the Software Verifier (SP-021)
using a checklist derived from EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.5.
Verifier: <Name, Organisation, independence evidence — see SP-021>
Checklist reference: <document ID or tool reference>
<<<
BASIC: --
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection, Review
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.5 and Table A.1, doc 20 – Source Code Verification Report.

[REQUIREMENT]
UID: CI-091
STATUS: Draft
TITLE: Verification records and verdict
STATEMENT: >>>
The Software Source Code Verification Report shall include:

  - Date and revision of the source code baseline, test report, and all
    supporting evidence reviewed.
  - Name, role, and independence evidence of the verifier (per SP-021).
  - Checklist results: each item marked Pass / Fail / N/A with observations.
  - Metrics confirmation:
      - All structural metrics within limits (CI-021): confirmed.
      - Coverage objectives met (CI-060): confirmed.
      - Performance budgets met (CI-070): confirmed.
  - List of findings: unique identifier, description, severity, and status.
  - Action items raised, with reference to the action item register.
  - Resolution evidence for all Critical and Major findings.
  - Overall verdict: Approved / Approved with conditions / Not approved.

The source code baseline and Component Test Report shall not be released and
integration testing (EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.6) shall not commence until an
Approved verdict is recorded.

Verification Report reference: <document ID>
Verdict: <to be completed upon review>
Date of approval: <YYYY-MM-DD>
<<<
BASIC: --
SIL_1: HR
SIL_2: HR
SIL_3: HR
SIL_4: HR
VERIFICATION_METHOD: Inspection, Review
RATIONALE: EN 50716:2023, Clause 7.5 and Table A.1, doc 20 – Source Code Verification Report.

